<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-08T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2928: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from">Colonel E. M.
                                    House</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-08T16:00:00+00:00">December 8, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 8—2:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>240. Your 141, December 7, 6 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d236fn2">Not
                                printed.</note> You may advise <persName corresp="#p_DGD1">da
                                Gama</persName> that I will press this matter<note n="3" xml:id="d236fn3">i. e., Brazilian representation at the preliminary
                                conference.</note> and see if it can be arranged.</p>
                        <p>There is considerable opposition here to bringing into the preliminary
                            conference but the great Allied powers and the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>